printf("Enter some text (Ctrl+D or Ctrl+Z to end on Unix/Windows):\n");

EOF is signaled on

        On Unix -
    like systems(Linux, macOS, etc.),
    you can signal EOF by pressing Ctrl +
        D(Control key and 'D' key simultaneously) at the beginning of a
        new line.

        On Windows,
    you can signal EOF by pressing Ctrl +
            Z(Control key and 'Z' key simultaneously) and
        then Enter.
